  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Does Walmart cash money orders?",
  "response": "Yes, many Walmart locations offer money services, including selling money orders through providers like MoneyGram and Walmart\u2019s own Money Services. However, when it comes to cashing money orders, Walmart\u2019s policies can vary by location:\n\n1. **Cashing Walmart Money Orders:** If you have a Walmart-issued money order, you can typically cash it at their Money Services counter. You will need to provide a valid photo ID and may be subject to transaction limits.\n\n2. **Cashing Third-Party Money Orders:** Walmart generally does **not** cash money orders issued by other providers (e.g., Western Union, USPS) unless the store has specifically enabled that service. It's best to check with your local Walmart to confirm.\n\n3. **Alternative Options:** If Walmart cannot cash your money order, you might consider other options such as banks, credit unions, check-cashing stores, or the issuer of the money order itself.\n\n**Tips:**\n\n- **Bring Identification:** Always have a valid photo ID (like a driver\u2019s license or passport) when attempting to cash a money order.\n  \n- **Check Fees:** Be aware that there may be fees associated with cashing money orders, depending on the service provider and the specific Walmart location.\n\n- **Verify Services Locally:** Since services can vary by store, it\u2019s a good idea to call your local Walmart or visit their [Money Services page](https://www.walmart.com/service/money-services) for the most accurate and up-to-date information.\n\n**Contact Walmart:**\n- **Website:** [Walmart Money Services](https://www.walmart.com/service/money-services)\n- **Customer Service:** You can reach out through Walmart's customer service for specific inquiries related to money orders and their cashing policies.\n\nBy verifying with your local store, you can ensure you have the most accurate information regarding their available money services.",
